还没
Still MIA

12:32.220 --> 12:33.410
你可以另找一只
You could always get another

12:33.420 --> 12:36.310
我并不想要其他的
I don't want another

12:36.320 --> 12:37.710
而且那样毫无意义
Besides, it's a moot point

12:37.720 --> 12:39.410
她已经在我心中根深蒂固
She was grandfathered

12:39.420 --> 12:41.410
她不在了 也不要别的宠物
Once she's gone, no more pets

12:41.420 --> 12:44.210
如果你出狱了  这就不是个问题了
Wouldn't be an issue if you were on the outside

12:44.220 --> 12:47.650
还在打那个主意啊?
Still tugging on that leash, eh?

12:47.660 --> 12:49.580
是的
Yup

12:49.590 --> 12:51.380
而这一次
And this is the part

12:51.390 --> 12:53.580
我正式向你发出邀请
where I extend a formal invitation

12:53.590 --> 12:55.880
你仍觉得我是大盗库珀么?
Cos you still think I'm DB Cooper?

12:55.890 --> 12:59.210
我不是觉得  是知道
I don't think. I know

12:59.220 --> 13:00.880
据我所知
The way I see it

13:00.890 --> 13:02.810
由于你开车撞死人
you're in here doing 60 to life

13:02.820 --> 13:04.210
被判60年至终身监禁
for vehicular manslaughter

13:04.220 --> 13:06.110
原该判你20年
It would have been 20

13:06.120 --> 13:07.810
但你的车是偷来的
but the car you were in was stolen

13:07.820 --> 13:10.610
变成犯另一重罪的谋杀
Felony murder rule cubes every sentence

13:10.620 --> 13:11.780
所以你还在这里
And here you are

13:11.790 --> 13:14.910
撞死那个女人是个意外
Hitting that woman was an accident

13:14.920 --> 13:16.750
但那车?
But the car?

13:16.760 --> 13:18.610
没人会无缘无故偷车的
No one accidentally steals a car

13:18.620 --> 13:20.410
问题就出现在这
So the question is

13:20.420 --> 13:23.510
为什么查尔斯 韦斯特莫兰德会
why would Charles Westmoreland be in Arizona boosting a car

13:23.520 --> 13:26.380
在他住处十个州外
ten states away from where he lived

13:26.390 --> 13:28.480
离墨西哥边境10英里远的亚利桑拿州开车狂飚呢?
and only ten miles from the Mexican border

13:28.490 --> 13:30.110
还有  为什么事情发生的两天前
And why, two days before that

13:30.120 --> 13:31.850
有人从波特兰一汽车旅馆
would someone make a phone call

13:31.860 --> 13:34.250
打电话给他妻子
to his wife from a motel in Portland

13:34.260 --> 13:37.280
而这旅馆恰巧在飞机场附近呢?
a stone's throw away from the airport out of which

13:37.290 --> 13:38.710
而电话后不久
 shortly after

13:38.720 --> 13:41.780
305航班被一个叫库珀的人劫持
flight 305 was hijacked by one DB Cooper

13:41.790 --> 13:44.180
飞机被劫后七小时
Seven hours after the hijacking

13:44.190 --> 13:47.380
记录表明查尔斯 韦斯特莫兰德
records show Charles Westmoreland

13:47.390 --> 13:49.680
因膝盖受伤在杨百翰市一家小诊所受过治疗
was treated for a busted knee at a free clinic in Brigham City

13:49.690 --> 13:51.210
七小时内  要从波特兰  俄勒冈
Only way to get from Portland, Oregon to Brigham City

13:51.220 --> 13:53.810
到犹他州的杨百翰市
Utah in seven hours

13:53.820 --> 13:57.680
除了开一辆打破世界记录的汽车
is in a car breaking every land speed record

13:57.690 --> 14:00.150
还有就是坐飞机
known to man,or flying

14:00.160 --> 14:02.210
大家都知道库珀
It's public record DB Cooper

14:02.220 --> 14:04.610
在起飞后一小时从那架727飞机跳出
jumped out of that 727 about an hour after take off

14:04.620 --> 14:05.980
在10000英尺的高空
Taking a dive at 10,000 feet

14:05.990 --> 14:09.580
拿着150万美金  跳了伞
with 1.5 million in cash

14:09.590 --> 14:11.980
而降落伞是仓促中装备的
and a hastily packed parachute

14:11.990 --> 14:13.810
可能降落得很不理想
might make for a pretty rough landing

14:13.820 --> 14:15.550
不理想到摔坏了骨头
Rough enough to shatter some bones

14:15.560 --> 14:17.310
可能就是左膝
Maybe even a left knee

14:17.320 --> 14:21.380
落地时  库珀将安排车来接他
DB Cooper would have had a car waiting for him

14:21.390 --> 14:24.110
根据1971年DMV记录
According to DMV records, in 1971

14:24.120 --> 14:27.980
查尔斯·韦斯特莫兰德很荣幸的 是一辆65年产雪佛莱的主人
Charles Westmoreland was the proud owner of a 65 Chevy Nova

14:27.990 --> 14:31.550
而在阿利桑那州边界 发现一辆65年产的雪佛莱
As it happens, a 65 Chevy Nova

14:31.560 --> 14:32.980
车牌已被刮花
with the registration number scraped off

14:32.990 --> 14:35.210
被抛弃在一旁
was found abandoned with a blown gasket

14:35.220 --> 14:36.950
气缸爆了
along the Arizona border

14:36.960 --> 14:40.910
就在你用偷来的车 撞到那女人的地方
a mile or two away from where you accidentally hit that woman

14:40.920 --> 14:44.320
一两里开外
with your stolen car

14:45.260 --> 14:47.180
这故事有意思
Interesting story

14:47.190 --> 14:49.250
这人更有意思
Interesting man

14:49.260 --> 14:52.510
但有一点你解释不了
But you didn't answer one thing

14:52.520 --> 14:54.050
是什么?
What's that?

14:54.060 --> 14:57.510
可能我确实伤到了膝盖
Maybe I did hurt my knee

14:57.520 --> 15:00.310
我确实偷了车
I did steal that car

15:00.320 --> 15:03.180
我也确实意外的撞了那可怜的女人
and I did accidentally hit that poor lady

15:03.190 --> 15:08.500
但是我11月24日
But how could I have hijacked a plane in Portland on November 24th

15:08.510 --> 15:10.080
我因为醉酒闹事被判监禁30天
when I was in Folsom

15:10.090 --> 15:14.890
又怎么能去波特兰劫持飞机呢?
finishing up a 30-day drunk and disorderly?

15:17.790 --> 15:21.410
我希望你不要把所有的越狱希望 都寄托在那笔钱上
I hope you weren't hanging this whole escape on that money

15:21.420 --> 15:25.060
因为我不是拥有者
cos I'm not the one in possession of it

15:27.320 --> 15:30.420
不过还是谢谢你的邀请
Thanks for the invite, though

15:45.260 --> 15:48.360
维罗妮卡
Veronica

15:50.090 --> 15:53.820
维罗妮卡  别这样
Veronica, come on

15:57.820 --> 15:58.980
我们没事了
We're OK

15:58.990 --> 16:01.950
这怎么算没事呢  尼克?
How is this OK, Nick?

16:01.960 --> 16:03.850
有人要杀我们
Somebody just tried to kill us

16:03.860 --> 16:05.980
-我知道  我在现场  -那就不要当作没事  好吗?
-I know. I was there.  -Then act like it,OK?

16:05.990 --> 16:10.450
我们眼睁睁的看着一个人 在我们面前被烧死
We just watched a man burn to death right in front of us

16:10.460 --> 16:13.660
我的天
My God

16:13.890 --> 16:16.450
卢卡斯   我的天啊
Lukasz... My God

16:16.460 --> 16:18.410
没事了  没事了  没事了
It's OK. It's OK

16:18.420 --> 16:19.850
我们居然抛下他不管
We just left him there

16:19.860 --> 16:24.490
我们为他做什么都于事无补 他一开门就没了命
There was nothing we could do.He was dead as soon as he opened the door

16:24.500 --> 16:27.200
我很想弄清楚这一切怎么回事 尼克
I am trying so hard to understand all this,Nick.

16:27.210 --> 16:29.410
这些人到底是谁  他们想干什么
Who these people are, what they want

16:29.420 --> 16:31.490
我们怎么可以不报警就离开那里了呢?
How we walked away without calling the police

16:31.500 --> 16:35.480
我们这么做是因为我们惹的 这些人不杀了我们是不会罢手的
We did it because these people we're dealing with won't stop until we're dead

16:35.490 --> 16:37.850
现在  如果他们认为我们死了 就像现在我们看上去好像是死了一样
If they think we're dead  like they do right now,

16:37.860 --> 16:40.490
可能我们就有点喘息的空间 我们来想想下一步怎么做
maybe we get a little breathing room here, we figure out what our next move is.

16:40.500 --> 16:41.690
不  我们应该去报警
We should go to the police

16:41.700 --> 16:43.350
我一直以来也是像你那样想的
I've been thinking the same thing

16:43.360 --> 16:48.260
但是  你知道吗 警察是斗不过他们的
But you know what?They're bigger than the police

16:48.560 --> 16:51.680
如果我们去报警 我们这么做
We go to the authorities and all we're gonna be doing

16:51.690 --> 16:53.780
就是告诉他们我们还活着
it's broadcast to them that we're still alive

16:53.790 --> 16:57.990
这样  我们又成为他们暗杀的目标了
and then we got that target right on our backs again

16:58.360 --> 16:59.880
我们不能永远躲下去
We can't hide forever

16:59.890 --> 17:01.980
不  不  可能不必永远躲
No, no. Maybe not forever

17:01.990 --> 17:04.510
不过我知道有个地方
But...I think I know a place we can

17:04.520 --> 17:08.120
可以让我们躲一阵子
at least for a little while

17:10.720 --> 17:13.180
我们只须自己混进去了
We just have to go in there ourselves then

17:13.190 --> 17:16.080
我说了  除非那老人加入 否则是不可能的
Like I said,unless the old man's in it's not possible

17:16.090 --> 17:18.280
而且即使可以进去 那里有守卫
And even if it were, the guards in there

17:18.290 --> 17:20.510
不会看不见我们在他们眼皮底下纵火
won't just sit back and watch us start a fire

17:20.520 --> 17:22.580
这点我已经想到解决办法
See, I already figured that part out

17:22.590 --> 17:23.880
我一直在想的
I been thinking

17:23.890 --> 17:25.500
怎么解决?
 And?

17:25.920 --> 17:28.350
还记得你在主教的办公室做的那事吗?
That thing you're doing in the Pope's office

17:28.360 --> 17:29.480
使用橡胶粘合剂?
You using rubber cement?

17:29.490 --> 17:30.200
然后?
Yeah

17:30.210 --> 17:32.410
-你能弄点出来吗?  -也许可以  为什么这么问?
-Can you get some out?  -Maybe. Why?

17:32.420 --> 17:35.250
守卫室有个咖啡壶  对吗?
Look, there's a coffee maker in the guards' room, right?

17:35.260 --> 17:36.000
我认识一位朋友
I got a hook-up

17:36.000 --> 17:38.710
在厨房里面干活
with one of my boys in the kitchen

17:38.720 --> 17:41.810
如果我们能涂点橡胶粘合剂在咖啡壶底部
If we can get rubber cement in the bottom of that coffee pot

17:41.820 --> 17:44.690
加热装置一打开...
when the burner goes on...

17:45.020 --> 17:47.380
这主意不错
It's a good idea

17:47.390 --> 17:49.050
但没有韦斯特莫兰德
But without Westmoreland

17:49.060 --> 17:51.010
我们进不去那房子的
we're never getting in that room

17:51.020 --> 17:52.410
他不想成为出逃的一份子?
 He doesn't want any part of this?

17:52.420 --> 17:53.510
不想
 No

17:53.520 --> 17:54.980
那他想要什么?
Then what does he want?

17:54.990 --> 17:57.610
他必有所求
He's gotta want something

17:57.620 --> 18:01.920
每个人都有其所求
Everybody wants something

18:08.500 --> 18:10.500
过来
come on

18:16.500 --> 18:18.000
真乖
That's a good girl.

18:26.290 --> 18:29.420
真想不到
I don't believe it

18:29.960 --> 18:30.660
谢谢
Thank you

18:30.660 --> 18:32.080
不客气
You're welcome

18:32.090 --> 18:33.310
你在哪里找到她的?
Where'd you find her?

18:33.320 --> 18:35.110
在礼拜堂旁边的院子里
In the yard, by the chapel

18:35.120 --> 18:40.010
为什么我感觉像有什么企图
Why do I get the feeling there's a string attached to this?

18:40.020 --> 18:44.590
没什么企图  举手之劳
Not a string. Just a favour

18:46.320 --> 18:48.210
我不是 库珀
 I'm not DB Cooper

18:48.220 --> 18:49.980
没关系
That's all right

18:49.990 --> 18:52.580
因为我想要做的
Cos it's not gonna take DB Cooper

18:52.590 --> 18:54.410
不必拜托到  库珀
to do what I need done

18:54.420 --> 18:56.210
什么事?
What's that?

18:56.220 --> 18:58.750
我只要你在指定时间
All I want you to do

18:58.760 --> 19:02.210
拿指定的咖啡壶进守卫室
is take a certain coffee pot into the guard room at a certain time

19:02.220 --> 19:03.810
然后打开加热装置
and turn the burner on

19:03.820 --> 19:05.450
为什么要这么做?
Why?

19:05.460 --> 19:07.850
如果那里失火的话
Let's just say it'd be in everyone's best interests

19:07.860 --> 19:09.850
我想这对大家都最好不过了
if a fire were to start in there

19:09.860 --> 19:13.510
猫儿  你觉得他像火神吗?
Marilyn, did you think he was the arsonist type?

19:13.520 --> 19:16.810
我不是
I'm not

19:16.820 --> 19:19.210
我是清道夫
I'm the cleanup crew type

19:19.220 --> 19:23.190
能从各种渠道搞到工具的人
The type that gets access to all kinds of tools

19:23.920 --> 19:25.780
迈克尔  非常感谢你找回小猫
Michael, I'm grateful for this

19:25.790 --> 19:27.580
真的
I really am

19:27.590 --> 19:30.080
自从我进来这地方
but I've made it a point to keep my nose clean

19:30.090 --> 19:32.250
我就打定主意不惹事生非
ever since I walked into this place

19:32.260 --> 19:34.610
32年来没有过不良记录
32 years without a blemish

19:34.620 --> 19:38.550
我希望有条件成为 假释榜上面的人
If that parole board date ever comes,I want to be ready

19:38.560 --> 19:40.710
我不能坏了这个大事
I can'tjeopardise that

19:40.720 --> 19:44.120
对不起
Sorry

19:48.090 --> 19:50.150
迈克尔
Michael

19:50.160 --> 19:53.690
还是很谢谢你  真的
Thanks, though. Really

19:56.690 --> 19:58.510
经历了那场骚乱
After what you went through in the riot

19:58.520 --> 20:00.380
我还以为你会请一天假
I thought you'd take a day off

20:00.390 --> 20:03.310
我没事
I'm fine

20:03.320 --> 20:04.850
同时也
I, uh...

20:04.860 --> 20:08.020
找不到人来代替我
I couldn't find anybody to cover for me, anyway

20:08.760 --> 20:11.180
希望你不会觉得你欠我什么
I hope you don't feel like you owe me anything

20:11.190 --> 20:13.580
当然没有
I do

20:13.590 --> 20:17.620
我...
I'm, uh...

20:17.960 --> 20:23.760
真的很感激你为我做的事
I really appreciate what you did for me

20:25.260 --> 20:27.990
不过呢?
But?

20:29.020 --> 20:32.310
但是你告诉我
But you told me that

20:32.320 --> 20:34.750
你跟P.I.去过水管槽隙
you had been up in the crawlspace for PI

20:34.760 --> 20:40.390
而P.I.是不会被派到那里的
and PI was never assigned to go there

20:43.260 --> 20:45.110
针打完了  对吗?
We're done here, right?

20:45.120 --> 20:47.510
迈克尔  不要这样
Michael, don't be like that

20:47.520 --> 20:50.450
我只是想知道一些答案
I just... I just want some answers

20:50.460 --> 20:54.020
谢谢你打的针  医生
Thanks for the shot, Doc

20:56.790 --> 20:59.050
我叫苏·帕尔森 要闻报的
Sue Parsons, Headline Press

20:59.060 --> 21:01.110
谢谢你的到来
Thanks for coming by

21:01.120 --> 21:03.280
感谢你给我时间
I appreciate you taking the time

21:03.290 --> 21:05.310
很感激你关注我的案子
I appreciate you looking at my case

21:05.320 --> 21:07.450
你有什么要说的?
So what can you tell me?

21:07.460 --> 21:09.680
据我所知  有很多人
From what I understand,you have numerous people

21:09.690 --> 21:11.810
在为你奔走
working on your behalf as we speak

21:11.820 --> 21:13.310
对
Yeah. Um, well...

21:13.320 --> 21:15.210
维罗妮卡·多诺万  她是我的代表律师
Veronica Donovan, she's my attorney

21:15.220 --> 21:16.950
尼克·萨维恩
and Nick Savrinn

21:16.960 --> 21:19.480
他在正义计划工作
He works at Project Justice

21:19.490 --> 21:21.950
萨维恩  好的
Savrinn. OK

21:21.960 --> 21:23.580
他们有什么进展吗?
Have they gotten very far?

21:23.590 --> 21:26.350
还没有什么可以提交到法庭的 还没有
Nothing to go to court with. Not yet, anyway

21:26.360 --> 21:31.510
你想过是时候放手了吗?
You ever think it's just time to let go?

21:31.520 --> 21:32.910
接受发生过的事实?
Accept what happened?

21:32.920 --> 21:34.350
放手?  是的
Let go, yeah

21:34.360 --> 21:36.850
接受发生过的事实?  从来没有
Accept what happened? Never

